The Ogun State Governor, Prince Dapo Abiodun, yesterday, ordered an immediate investigation into the collapse of a building that was undergoing an illegal demolition by the owners, at Iperu, in Ikenne Local Council. The collapse of the one-storey building along Ogere Road, led to the death of two people, last Thursday.  The four-man team constituted by Abiodun, according to a statement by his Chief Press Secretary, Kunle Somorin, comprises the state Commissioner for Physical Planning, TPL Tunji Odunlami; Special Adviser on Environment, Mr. Ola Oresanya; Special Adviser, Bureau of Lands and Survey, Mr. Ololade Salami, and the Commissioner of Police, Mr. Lanre Bankole. The committee is to determine the remote and immediate causes of the building collapse and report back in one week. While commiserating with the families of the deceased over the unfortunate loss of their loved ones, Abiodun assured that anyone found guilty of,Â or culpable in the incident will be dealt with according to the law.